sentences: Greg Nelson (born September 10, 1948) is a music producer from Nashville.
In 1994 with the Nashville-based Christian songwriter Bob Farrell he composed produced and recorded Saviour, described as a modern oratorio or christian musical.
Nelson began serving in a dual role at LifeWay Worship in 2004 as an exclusive songwriter and as Creative Supervisor for song and writer development.
Nelson was inducted into the Gospel Music Hall of Fame in 2018.
